license: MIT
keywords:
  - computational simulation
  - collective control
  - latency
  - vector aggregation
  - mechanism validation
  - reduced-order model
abstract: >
  Code, deterministic seeds and simulation outputs reproducing the study of a
  coordinated contrarian minority that stabilizes latency- and curvature-induced
  overshoot in crowd-sourced continuous control. Includes the confirmatory grid
  (MC=50), quantization ablation, frame-level rate-damping evidence, generality
  sweeps, and the reduced-order (small-signal) stability analysis.
